    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Considerations for Supporting a Buyer's Cart Experience\n Allow a Buyer to Create a Wish List of Items for a Future Cart\n Email a Buyer for an Abandoned Cart\n Enforce Quantity Rules When a Buyer Adds Products to a Cart or Wish...\n Set Product Prices in the Cart from an External Source\n Allow a B2B Commerce for Visualforce Guest Buyer to Maintain a Cart\n Allow a B2B Commerce for Visualforce Guest Buyer to Check Out\n Standard Checkout versus Line-Level Independence (LLI) Checkout\n Calculate Tax at Checkout\n Set Up Payment Types for Storefront Purchases\n Fulfill a Buyer's Order\n Scale Your Cart Capabilities for a Large Number of Items\n Enable Cart Scale\n Checkout with Cart Scale\n Enable Asynchronous Order Placement for Checkout\n Considerations for Asynchronous Processing for Carts and Orders\n Generate an Invoice for a Buyer's Order\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nCheckout with Cart Scale\n\nWhen you enable Cart Scale, the default workflow for standard checkout is modified to accommodate a cart with a large number of items.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13) only\n\nNOTE Line-level independence (LLI) checkout isn't compatible with Cart Scale.\nCart Validation before Checkout\n\nThe cart's price and availability data must be current before a buyer can begin checkout. When the buyer clicks Checkout from the Scaled Cart page, a remote action evaluates the specified asynchronous processing threshold, which determines how the validation executes:\n\nWhen the number of cart items is less than the asynchronous processing threshold, the refresh logic executes synchronously. The Scaled Cart page automatically updates with the current price and availability data. If no errors occur, the buyer can continue to the Checkout page.\nWhen the number of cart items is equal to or exceeds the asynchronous processing threshold, the buyer is prompted to refresh the price and availability data for all cart items. The buyer can either proceed or cancel and manually click Refresh Cart from the Scaled Cart page. The refresh logic executes asynchronously. The Scaled Cart page becomes inactive, except for the Continue Shopping button, and indicates that the refresh operation is in progress. After the refresh operation completes, the buyer can click Checkout from the Scaled Cart page again to continue to the Checkout page.\nNOTE\nFor more information about refreshing the cart's price and availability data, see Full Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page.\nThe Scaled Cart page evaluates your selected reprice strategy for ensuring that the cart's price data is current. However, a reprice strategy of Always prevents Cart Scale's synchronous portion of checkout from proceeding. Avoid using the Always strategy when you enable Cart Scale. For more information about reprice strategies, see Optimize How Frequently the Shopping Cart Page Calls Price Logic.\nWhen the buyer is a guest, asynchronous processing isn't supported. Clicking Checkout from the Scaled Cart page always executes synchronous processing, which automatically updates the current price and availability data.\nOrder Review\n\nIn the Order Review section of the standard Checkout page, all product information is hidden. The buyer's contact information, billing address, and shipping address remain available.\n\nOrder Confirmation\n\nWhen you enable Cart Scale, the logic that converts a cart to an order—order placement—also executes synchronously or asynchronously, depending on the asynchronous processing threshold:\n\nWhen the number of cart items is less than the asynchronous processing threshold, the order placement logic executes synchronously.\nWhen the number of cart items is equal to or exceeds the asynchronous processing threshold, the order placement logic executes asynchronously.\n\nIn the Order Confirmation section of the standard Checkout page, the information shown depends on whether the logic executes asynchronously and when the asynchronous process completes. See Show Order Confirmation Details and Send Order Emails.\n\nSEE ALSO\nStandard Checkout versus Line-Level Independence (LLI) Checkout\nCheckout Page\nFull Refresh of a Cart's Data on the Scaled Cart Page\nOptimize How Frequently the Shopping Cart Page Calls Price Logic\nShow Order Confirmation Details and Send Order Emails\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
